0.3333....
0.3333...=\frac{1}{3}
\frac{3}{10} + \frac{3}{100} + \frac{3}{1000} + \cdots
a_1 = \frac{3}{10}
r=\frac{1}{10}
\sum =\frac{a_1}{1-r}=\frac{3}{10}\times\frac{10}{9} =\frac{1}{3}
0.111\ldots
10\times0.111\ldots=1.111\ldots
9\times0.111\ldots=1.000\ldots=1
0.111\ldots=1/9
0.333\ldots=0.\overline{3}
10\times0.\overline{3}=3.\overline{3}
9\times0.\overline{3}=3.\overline{0}=3
0.\overline{3}=3/9=1/3
\frac{1}{3}=0.33333\ldots
0.33333=\frac{1}{3}
3+0.33333...=\sum_{i=0}^N\frac{3}{10^n}\quad\text{where N}\to\infty
=3\sum_{n=0}^N\frac{1}{10^n}
=3\sum_{n=0}^N(\frac{1}{10})^n
1+a^2+a^3....a^n=\frac{a^{n+1}-1}{a-1}
=3\cdot \frac{(\frac{1}{10})^{N+1}-1}{\frac{1}{10}-1}
=3\cdot \frac{(\frac{1}{10})^{N+1}-1}{\frac{1-10}{10}}
=3\cdot \frac{((\frac{1}{10})^{N+1}-1)*10}{1-10}
=3\cdot \frac{(1-(\frac{1}{10})^{N+1})*10}{9}
N\to\infty;(\frac{1}{10})^{N+1}\to0
=3\cdot \lim_{N\to\infty}\frac{(1-(\frac{1}{10})^{N+1})*10}{9}
=3\cdot \frac{10}{9}
=\frac{10}{3}
\Rightarrow 3+0.33333...=\frac{10}{3}
\Rightarrow 0.33333...=\frac{10}{3}-3
\Rightarrow 0.33333...=\frac{10-9}{3}
\Rightarrow 0.33333...=\frac{1}{3}
0.999\ldots=1
